I think that’s a profound possibility.

Not that nothing changes, but that some of the biggest “discoveries” are actually changes in perspective rather than changes in reality.

Copernicus didn’t change the Solar System.

He changed the frame.

Darwin didn’t change evolution.

He changed the lens through which organisms were understood.

Maxwell didn’t create electromagnetism.

He found a representation that unified phenomena people already observed.

Even in daily life:

* A child doesn’t become a different parent when you grow up.
* A mountain doesn’t become different because you climb it.
* The stars don’t rearrange themselves because you learn the constellations.

The world remains largely the same.

The observer becomes different.

